21// v0.8h: Y
22// v1.16b: 8U, 8V
23
24// Read 8 Y, 4 U and 4 V from 422
25#define READYUV422 \
26 "ldr d0, [%[src_y]], #8 \n" \
27 "ld1 {v1.s}[0], [%[src_u]], #4 \n" \
28 "ld1 {v1.s}[1], [%[src_v]], #4 \n" \
29 "zip1 v0.16b, v0.16b, v0.16b \n" \
30 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_y], 448] \n" \
31 "zip1 v1.16b, v1.16b, v1.16b \n" \
32 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_u], 128] \n" \
33 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_v], 128] \n"
34
35// Read 8 Y, 8 U and 8 V from 444
36#define READYUV444 \
37 "ldr d0, [%[src_y]], #8 \n" \
38 "ld1 {v1.d}[0], [%[src_u]], #8 \n" \
39 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_y], 448] \n" \
40 "ld1 {v1.d}[1], [%[src_v]], #8 \n" \
41 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_u], 448] \n" \
42 "zip1 v0.16b, v0.16b, v0.16b \n" \
43 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_v], 448] \n"
44
45// Read 8 Y, and set 4 U and 4 V to 128
46#define READYUV400 \
47 "ldr d0, [%[src_y]], #8 \n" \
48 "movi v1.16b, #128 \n" \
49 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_y], 448] \n" \
50 "zip1 v0.16b, v0.16b, v0.16b \n"
51
52static const uvec8 kNV12Table = {0, 0, 2, 2, 4, 4, 6, 6,
53 1, 1, 3, 3, 5, 5, 7, 7};
54static const uvec8 kNV21Table = {1, 1, 3, 3, 5, 5, 7, 7,
55 0, 0, 2, 2, 4, 4, 6, 6};
56
57// Read 8 Y and 4 UV from NV12 or NV21
58#define READNV12 \
59 "ldr d0, [%[src_y]], #8 \n" \
60 "ldr d1, [%[src_uv]], #8 \n" \
61 "zip1 v0.16b, v0.16b, v0.16b \n" \
62 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_y], 448] \n" \
63 "tbl v1.16b, {v1.16b}, v2.16b \n" \
64 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_uv], 448] \n"
65
66// Read 8 YUY2
67#define READYUY2 \
68 "ld2 {v0.8b, v1.8b}, [%[src_yuy2]], #16 \n" \
69 "zip1 v0.16b, v0.16b, v0.16b \n" \
70 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_yuy2], 448] \n" \
71 "tbl v1.16b, {v1.16b}, v2.16b \n"
72
73// Read 8 UYVY
74#define READUYVY \
75 "ld2 {v3.8b, v4.8b}, [%[src_uyvy]], #16 \n" \
76 "zip1 v0.16b, v4.16b, v4.16b \n" \
77 "prfm pldl1keep, [%[src_uyvy], 448] \n" \
78 "tbl v1.16b, {v3.16b}, v2.16b \n"
79
80// UB VR UG VG
81// YG BB BG BR
82#define YUVTORGB_SETUP \
83 "ld4r {v28.16b, v29.16b, v30.16b, v31.16b}, [%[kUVCoeff]] \n" \
84 "ld4r {v24.8h, v25.8h, v26.8h, v27.8h}, [%[kRGBCoeffBias]] \n"
85
86// v16.8h: B
87// v17.8h: G
88// v18.8h: R
89
90// Convert from YUV to 2.14 fixed point RGB
91#define YUVTORGB \
92 "umull2 v3.4s, v0.8h, v24.8h \n" \
93 "umull v6.8h, v1.8b, v30.8b \n" \
94 "umull v0.4s, v0.4h, v24.4h \n" \
95 "umlal2 v6.8h, v1.16b, v31.16b \n" /* DG */ \
96 "uqshrn v0.4h, v0.4s, #16 \n" \
97 "uqshrn2 v0.8h, v3.4s, #16 \n" /* Y */ \
98 "umull v4.8h, v1.8b, v28.8b \n" /* DB */ \
99 "umull2 v5.8h, v1.16b, v29.16b \n" /* DR */ \
100 "add v17.8h, v0.8h, v26.8h \n" /* G */ \
101 "add v16.8h, v0.8h, v4.8h \n" /* B */ \
102 "add v18.8h, v0.8h, v5.8h \n" /* R */ \
103 "uqsub v17.8h, v17.8h, v6.8h \n" /* G */ \
104 "uqsub v16.8h, v16.8h, v25.8h \n" /* B */ \
105 "uqsub v18.8h, v18.8h, v27.8h \n" /* R */
106
107// Convert from 2.14 fixed point RGB To 8 bit RGB
108#define RGBTORGB8 \
109 "uqshrn v17.8b, v17.8h, #6 \n" \
110 "uqshrn v16.8b, v16.8h, #6 \n" \
111 "uqshrn v18.8b, v18.8h, #6 \n"
112
113#define YUVTORGB_REGS \
114 "v0", "v1", "v3", "v4", "v5", "v6", "v7", "v16", "v17", "v18", "v24", "v25", \
115 "v26", "v27", "v28", "v29", "v30", "v31"
116
117void I444ToARGBRow_NEON(const uint8_t* src_y,
118 const uint8_t* src_u,
119 const uint8_t* src_v,
120 uint8_t* dst_argb,
121 const struct YuvConstants* yuvconstants,
122 int width) {
123 asm volatile(
124 YUVTORGB_SETUP
125 "movi v19.8b, #255 \n" /* A */
126 "1: \n" READYUV444 YUVTORGB
127 RGBTORGB8
128 "subs %w[width], %w[width], #8 \n"
129 "st4 {v16.8b,v17.8b,v18.8b,v19.8b}, [%[dst_argb]], #32 \n"
130 "b.gt 1b \n"
131 : [src_y] "+r"(src_y), // %[src_y]
132 [src_u] "+r"(src_u), // %[src_u]
133 [src_v] "+r"(src_v), // %[src_v]
134 [dst_argb] "+r"(dst_argb), // %[dst_argb]
135 [width] "+r"(width) // %[width]
136 : [kUVCoeff] "r"(&yuvconstants->kUVCoeff), // %[kUVCoeff]
137 [kRGBCoeffBias] "r"(&yuvconstants->kRGBCoeffBias) // %[kRGBCoeffBias]
138 : "cc", "memory", YUVTORGB_REGS, "v19");
139}

327#define ARGBTOARGB4444 \
328 /* Input v16.8b<=B, v17.8b<=G, v18.8b<=R, v19.8b<=A, v23.8b<=0x0f */ \
329 "ushr v16.8b, v16.8b, #4 \n" /* B */ \
330 "bic v17.8b, v17.8b, v23.8b \n" /* G */ \
331 "ushr v18.8b, v18.8b, #4 \n" /* R */ \
332 "bic v19.8b, v19.8b, v23.8b \n" /* A */ \
333 "orr v0.8b, v16.8b, v17.8b \n" /* BG */ \
334 "orr v1.8b, v18.8b, v19.8b \n" /* RA */ \
335 "zip1 v0.16b, v0.16b, v1.16b \n" /* BGRA */

337void I422ToARGB4444Row_NEON(const uint8_t* src_y,
338 const uint8_t* src_u,
339 const uint8_t* src_v,
340 uint8_t* dst_argb4444,
341 const struct YuvConstants* yuvconstants,
342 int width) {
343 asm volatile(
344 YUVTORGB_SETUP
345 "movi v23.16b, #0x0f \n" // bits to clear with
346 // vbic.
347 "1: \n" READYUV422 YUVTORGB
348 RGBTORGB8
349 "subs %w[width], %w[width], #8 \n"
350 "movi v19.8b, #255 \n" ARGBTOARGB4444
351 "st1 {v0.8h}, [%[dst_argb4444]], #16 \n" // store 8
352 // pixels
353 // ARGB4444.
354 "b.gt 1b \n"
355 : [src_y] "+r"(src_y), // %[src_y]
356 [src_u] "+r"(src_u), // %[src_u]
357 [src_v] "+r"(src_v), // %[src_v]
358 [dst_argb4444] "+r"(dst_argb4444), // %[dst_argb4444]
359 [width] "+r"(width) // %[width]
360 : [kUVCoeff] "r"(&yuvconstants->kUVCoeff), // %[kUVCoeff]
361 [kRGBCoeffBias] "r"(&yuvconstants->kRGBCoeffBias) // %[kRGBCoeffBias]
362 : "cc", "memory", YUVTORGB_REGS, "v19", "v23");
363}

385void J400ToARGBRow_NEON(const uint8_t* src_y, uint8_t* dst_argb, int width) {
386 asm volatile(
387 "movi v23.8b, #255 \n"
388 "1: \n"
389 "ld1 {v20.8b}, [%0], #8 \n"
390 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
391 "orr v21.8b, v20.8b, v20.8b \n"
392 "orr v22.8b, v20.8b, v20.8b \n"
393 "subs %w2, %w2, #8 \n"
394 "st4 {v20.8b,v21.8b,v22.8b,v23.8b}, [%1], #32 \n"
395 "b.gt 1b \n"
396 : "+r"(src_y), // %0
397 "+r"(dst_argb), // %1
398 "+r"(width) // %2
399 :
400 : "cc", "memory", "v20", "v21", "v22", "v23");
401}

1046// Shuffle table for reversing the bytes.
1047static const uvec8 kShuffleMirror = {15u, 14u, 13u, 12u, 11u, 10u, 9u, 8u,
1048 7u, 6u, 5u, 4u, 3u, 2u, 1u, 0u};
1049
1050void MirrorRow_NEON(const uint8_t* src, uint8_t* dst, int width) {
1051 asm volatile(
1052 // Start at end of source row.
1053 "ld1 {v3.16b}, [%3] \n" // shuffler
1054 "add %0, %0, %w2, sxtw \n"
1055 "sub %0, %0, #32 \n"
1056 "1: \n"
1057 "ldr q2, [%0, 16] \n"
1058 "ldr q1, [%0], -32 \n" // src -= 32
1059 "subs %w2, %w2, #32 \n" // 32 pixels per loop.
1060 "tbl v0.16b, {v2.16b}, v3.16b \n"
1061 "tbl v1.16b, {v1.16b}, v3.16b \n"
1062 "st1 {v0.16b, v1.16b}, [%1], #32 \n" // store 32 pixels
1063 "b.gt 1b \n"
1064 : "+r"(src), // %0
1065 "+r"(dst), // %1
1066 "+r"(width) // %2
1067 : "r"(&kShuffleMirror) // %3
1068 : "cc", "memory", "v0", "v1", "v2", "v3");
1069}

1909#define RGBTOUV_SETUP_REG \
1910 "movi v20.8h, #56, lsl #0 \n" /* UB/VR coefficient (0.875) / 2 */ \
1911 "movi v21.8h, #37, lsl #0 \n" /* UG coefficient (-0.5781) / 2 */ \
1912 "movi v22.8h, #19, lsl #0 \n" /* UR coefficient (-0.2969) / 2 */ \
1913 "movi v23.8h, #9, lsl #0 \n" /* VB coefficient (-0.1406) / 2 */ \
1914 "movi v24.8h, #47, lsl #0 \n" /* VG coefficient (-0.7344) / 2 */ \
1915 "movi v25.16b, #0x80 \n" /* 128.5 (0x8080 in 16-bit) */
1916
1917// 16x2 pixels -> 8x1. width is number of argb pixels. e.g. 16.
1918// clang-format off
1919#define RGBTOUV(QB, QG, QR) \
1920 "mul v3.8h, " #QB ",v20.8h \n" /* B */ \
1921 "mul v4.8h, " #QR ",v20.8h \n" /* R */ \
1922 "mls v3.8h, " #QG ",v21.8h \n" /* G */ \
1923 "mls v4.8h, " #QG ",v24.8h \n" /* G */ \
1924 "mls v3.8h, " #QR ",v22.8h \n" /* R */ \
1925 "mls v4.8h, " #QB ",v23.8h \n" /* B */ \
1926 "add v3.8h, v3.8h, v25.8h \n" /* +128 -> unsigned */ \
1927 "add v4.8h, v4.8h, v25.8h \n" /* +128 -> unsigned */ \
1928 "uqshrn v0.8b, v3.8h, #8 \n" /* 16 bit to 8 bit U */ \
1929 "uqshrn v1.8b, v4.8h, #8 \n" /* 16 bit to 8 bit V */
1930// clang-format on
1931

1933// TODO(fbarchard): consider ptrdiff_t for all strides.

2641// Bilinear filter 16x2 -> 16x1
2642void InterpolateRow_NEON(uint8_t* dst_ptr,
2643 const uint8_t* src_ptr,
2644 ptrdiff_t src_stride,
2645 int dst_width,
2646 int source_y_fraction) {
2647 int y1_fraction = source_y_fraction;
2648 int y0_fraction = 256 - y1_fraction;
2649 const uint8_t* src_ptr1 = src_ptr + src_stride;
2650 asm volatile(
2651 "cmp %w4, #0 \n"
2652 "b.eq 100f \n"
2653 "cmp %w4, #128 \n"
2654 "b.eq 50f \n"
2655
2656 "dup v5.16b, %w4 \n"
2657 "dup v4.16b, %w5 \n"
2658 // General purpose row blend.
2659 "1: \n"
2660 "ld1 {v0.16b}, [%1], #16 \n"

2665 "umull2 v3.8h, v0.16b, v4.16b \n"
2666 "prfm pldl1keep, [%2, 448] \n"

2670 "rshrn2 v0.16b, v3.8h, #8 \n"
2671 "st1 {v0.16b}, [%0], #16 \n"
2672 "b.gt 1b \n"
2673 "b 99f \n"
2674
2675 // Blend 50 / 50.
2676 "50: \n"
2677 "ld1 {v0.16b}, [%1], #16 \n"
2678 "ld1 {v1.16b}, [%2], #16 \n"
2679 "subs %w3, %w3, #16 \n"
2680 "prfm pldl1keep, [%1, 448] \n"
2681 "urhadd v0.16b, v0.16b, v1.16b \n"
2682 "prfm pldl1keep, [%2, 448] \n"
2683 "st1 {v0.16b}, [%0], #16 \n"

2706// dr * (256 - sa) / 256 + sr = dr - dr * sa / 256 + sr
2707void ARGBBlendRow_NEON(const uint8_t* src_argb,
2708 const uint8_t* src_argb1,
2709 uint8_t* dst_argb,
2710 int width) {
2711 asm volatile(
2712 "subs %w3, %w3, #8 \n"
2713 "b.lt 89f \n"
2714 // Blend 8 pixels.
2715 "8: \n"
2716 "ld4 {v0.8b,v1.8b,v2.8b,v3.8b}, [%0], #32 \n" // load 8 ARGB0
2717 "ld4 {v4.8b,v5.8b,v6.8b,v7.8b}, [%1], #32 \n" // load 8 ARGB1
2718 "subs %w3, %w3, #8 \n" // 8 processed per loop.
2719 "umull v16.8h, v4.8b, v3.8b \n" // db * a
2720 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
2721 "umull v17.8h, v5.8b, v3.8b \n" // dg * a
2722 "prfm pldl1keep, [%1, 448] \n"
2723 "umull v18.8h, v6.8b, v3.8b \n" // dr * a
2724 "uqrshrn v16.8b, v16.8h, #8 \n" // db >>= 8
2725 "uqrshrn v17.8b, v17.8h, #8 \n" // dg >>= 8
2726 "uqrshrn v18.8b, v18.8h, #8 \n" // dr >>= 8
2727 "uqsub v4.8b, v4.8b, v16.8b \n" // db - (db * a / 256)
2728 "uqsub v5.8b, v5.8b, v17.8b \n" // dg - (dg * a / 256)
2729 "uqsub v6.8b, v6.8b, v18.8b \n" // dr - (dr * a / 256)
2730 "uqadd v0.8b, v0.8b, v4.8b \n" // + sb
2731 "uqadd v1.8b, v1.8b, v5.8b \n" // + sg
2732 "uqadd v2.8b, v2.8b, v6.8b \n" // + sr
2733 "movi v3.8b, #255 \n" // a = 255
2734 "st4 {v0.8b,v1.8b,v2.8b,v3.8b}, [%2], #32 \n" // store 8 ARGB
2735 // pixels
2736 "b.ge 8b \n"
2737
2738 "89: \n"
2739 "adds %w3, %w3, #8-1 \n"
2740 "b.lt 99f \n"
2741
2742 // Blend 1 pixels.
2743 "1: \n"
2744 "ld4 {v0.b,v1.b,v2.b,v3.b}[0], [%0], #4 \n" // load 1 pixel
2745 // ARGB0.
2746 "ld4 {v4.b,v5.b,v6.b,v7.b}[0], [%1], #4 \n" // load 1 pixel
2747 // ARGB1.
2748 "subs %w3, %w3, #1 \n" // 1 processed per loop.
2749 "umull v16.8h, v4.8b, v3.8b \n" // db * a
2750 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
2751 "umull v17.8h, v5.8b, v3.8b \n" // dg * a
2752 "prfm pldl1keep, [%1, 448] \n"
2753 "umull v18.8h, v6.8b, v3.8b \n" // dr * a
2754 "uqrshrn v16.8b, v16.8h, #8 \n" // db >>= 8
2755 "uqrshrn v17.8b, v17.8h, #8 \n" // dg >>= 8
2756 "uqrshrn v18.8b, v18.8h, #8 \n" // dr >>= 8
2757 "uqsub v4.8b, v4.8b, v16.8b \n" // db - (db * a / 256)
2758 "uqsub v5.8b, v5.8b, v17.8b \n" // dg - (dg * a / 256)
2759 "uqsub v6.8b, v6.8b, v18.8b \n" // dr - (dr * a / 256)
2760 "uqadd v0.8b, v0.8b, v4.8b \n" // + sb
2761 "uqadd v1.8b, v1.8b, v5.8b \n" // + sg
2762 "uqadd v2.8b, v2.8b, v6.8b \n" // + sr
2763 "movi v3.8b, #255 \n" // a = 255
2764 "st4 {v0.b,v1.b,v2.b,v3.b}[0], [%2], #4 \n" // store 1 pixel.
2765 "b.ge 1b \n"
2766
2767 "99: \n"
2768
2769 : "+r"(src_argb), // %0
2770 "+r"(src_argb1), // %1
2771 "+r"(dst_argb), // %2
2772 "+r"(width) // %3
2773 :
2774 : "cc", "memory", "v0", "v1", "v2", "v3", "v4", "v5", "v6", "v7", "v16",
2775 "v17", "v18");
2776}

2803// Quantize 8 ARGB pixels (32 bytes).
2804// dst = (dst * scale >> 16) * interval_size + interval_offset;
2805void ARGBQuantizeRow_NEON(uint8_t* dst_argb,
2806 int scale,
2807 int interval_size,
2808 int interval_offset,
2809 int width) {
2810 asm volatile(
2811 "dup v4.8h, %w2 \n"
2812 "ushr v4.8h, v4.8h, #1 \n" // scale >>= 1
2813 "dup v5.8h, %w3 \n" // interval multiply.
2814 "dup v6.8h, %w4 \n" // interval add
2815
2816 // 8 pixel loop.
2817 "1: \n"
2818 "ld4 {v0.8b,v1.8b,v2.8b,v3.8b}, [%0] \n" // load 8 ARGB.
2819 "subs %w1, %w1, #8 \n" // 8 processed per loop.
2820 "uxtl v0.8h, v0.8b \n" // b (0 .. 255)
2821 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
2822 "uxtl v1.8h, v1.8b \n"
2823 "uxtl v2.8h, v2.8b \n"
2824 "sqdmulh v0.8h, v0.8h, v4.8h \n" // b * scale
2825 "sqdmulh v1.8h, v1.8h, v4.8h \n" // g
2826 "sqdmulh v2.8h, v2.8h, v4.8h \n" // r
2827 "mul v0.8h, v0.8h, v5.8h \n" // b * interval_size
2828 "mul v1.8h, v1.8h, v5.8h \n" // g
2829 "mul v2.8h, v2.8h, v5.8h \n" // r
2830 "add v0.8h, v0.8h, v6.8h \n" // b + interval_offset
2831 "add v1.8h, v1.8h, v6.8h \n" // g
2832 "add v2.8h, v2.8h, v6.8h \n" // r
2833 "uqxtn v0.8b, v0.8h \n"
2834 "uqxtn v1.8b, v1.8h \n"
2835 "uqxtn v2.8b, v2.8h \n"
2836 "st4 {v0.8b,v1.8b,v2.8b,v3.8b}, [%0], #32 \n" // store 8 ARGB
2837 "b.gt 1b \n"
2838 : "+r"(dst_argb), // %0
2839 "+r"(width) // %1
2840 : "r"(scale), // %2
2841 "r"(interval_size), // %3
2842 "r"(interval_offset) // %4
2843 : "cc", "memory", "v0", "v1", "v2", "v3", "v4", "v5", "v6");
2844}

2846// Shade 8 pixels at a time by specified value.
2847// NOTE vqrdmulh.s16 q10, q10, d0[0] must use a scaler register from 0 to 8.
2848// Rounding in vqrdmulh does +1 to high if high bit of low s16 is set.
2849void ARGBShadeRow_NEON(const uint8_t* src_argb,
2850 uint8_t* dst_argb,
2851 int width,
2852 uint32_t value) {
2853 asm volatile(
2854 "dup v0.4s, %w3 \n" // duplicate scale value.
2855 "zip1 v0.8b, v0.8b, v0.8b \n" // v0.8b aarrggbb.
2856 "ushr v0.8h, v0.8h, #1 \n" // scale / 2.
2857
2858 // 8 pixel loop.
2859 "1: \n"
2860 "ld4 {v4.8b,v5.8b,v6.8b,v7.8b}, [%0], #32 \n" // load 8 ARGB
2861 "subs %w2, %w2, #8 \n" // 8 processed per loop.
2862 "uxtl v4.8h, v4.8b \n" // b (0 .. 255)
2863 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
2864 "uxtl v5.8h, v5.8b \n"
2865 "uxtl v6.8h, v6.8b \n"
2866 "uxtl v7.8h, v7.8b \n"
2867 "sqrdmulh v4.8h, v4.8h, v0.h[0] \n" // b * scale * 2
2868 "sqrdmulh v5.8h, v5.8h, v0.h[1] \n" // g
2869 "sqrdmulh v6.8h, v6.8h, v0.h[2] \n" // r
2870 "sqrdmulh v7.8h, v7.8h, v0.h[3] \n" // a
2871 "uqxtn v4.8b, v4.8h \n"
2872 "uqxtn v5.8b, v5.8h \n"
2873 "uqxtn v6.8b, v6.8h \n"
2874 "uqxtn v7.8b, v7.8h \n"
2875 "st4 {v4.8b,v5.8b,v6.8b,v7.8b}, [%1], #32 \n" // store 8 ARGB
2876 "b.gt 1b \n"
2877 : "+r"(src_argb), // %0
2878 "+r"(dst_argb), // %1
2879 "+r"(width) // %2
2880 : "r"(value) // %3
2881 : "cc", "memory", "v0", "v4", "v5", "v6", "v7");
2882}

2911// Convert 8 ARGB pixels (32 bytes) to 8 Sepia ARGB pixels.
2912// b = (r * 35 + g * 68 + b * 17) >> 7
2913// g = (r * 45 + g * 88 + b * 22) >> 7
2914// r = (r * 50 + g * 98 + b * 24) >> 7
2915
2916void ARGBSepiaRow_NEON(uint8_t* dst_argb, int width) {
2917 asm volatile(
2918 "movi v20.8b, #17 \n" // BB coefficient
2919 "movi v21.8b, #68 \n" // BG coefficient
2920 "movi v22.8b, #35 \n" // BR coefficient
2921 "movi v24.8b, #22 \n" // GB coefficient
2922 "movi v25.8b, #88 \n" // GG coefficient
2923 "movi v26.8b, #45 \n" // GR coefficient
2924 "movi v28.8b, #24 \n" // BB coefficient
2925 "movi v29.8b, #98 \n" // BG coefficient
2926 "movi v30.8b, #50 \n" // BR coefficient
2927 "1: \n"
2928 "ld4 {v0.8b,v1.8b,v2.8b,v3.8b}, [%0] \n" // load 8 ARGB pixels.
2929 "subs %w1, %w1, #8 \n" // 8 processed per loop.
2930 "umull v4.8h, v0.8b, v20.8b \n" // B to Sepia B
2931 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
2932 "umlal v4.8h, v1.8b, v21.8b \n" // G
2933 "umlal v4.8h, v2.8b, v22.8b \n" // R
2934 "umull v5.8h, v0.8b, v24.8b \n" // B to Sepia G
2935 "umlal v5.8h, v1.8b, v25.8b \n" // G
2936 "umlal v5.8h, v2.8b, v26.8b \n" // R
2937 "umull v6.8h, v0.8b, v28.8b \n" // B to Sepia R
2938 "umlal v6.8h, v1.8b, v29.8b \n" // G
2939 "umlal v6.8h, v2.8b, v30.8b \n" // R
2940 "uqshrn v0.8b, v4.8h, #7 \n" // 16 bit to 8 bit B
2941 "uqshrn v1.8b, v5.8h, #7 \n" // 16 bit to 8 bit G

2952// Tranform 8 ARGB pixels (32 bytes) with color matrix.
2953// TODO(fbarchard): Was same as Sepia except matrix is provided. This function
2954// needs to saturate. Consider doing a non-saturating version.
2955void ARGBColorMatrixRow_NEON(const uint8_t* src_argb,
2956 uint8_t* dst_argb,
2957 const int8_t* matrix_argb,
2958 int width) {
2959 asm volatile(
2960 "ld1 {v2.16b}, [%3] \n" // load 3 ARGB vectors.
2961 "sxtl v0.8h, v2.8b \n" // B,G coefficients s16.
2962 "sxtl2 v1.8h, v2.16b \n" // R,A coefficients s16.
2963
2964 "1: \n"
2965 "ld4 {v16.8b,v17.8b,v18.8b,v19.8b}, [%0], #32 \n" // load 8 ARGB
2966 "subs %w2, %w2, #8 \n" // 8 processed per loop.
2967 "uxtl v16.8h, v16.8b \n" // b (0 .. 255) 16 bit
2968 "prfm pldl1keep, [%0, 448] \n"
2969 "uxtl v17.8h, v17.8b \n" // g
2970 "uxtl v18.8h, v18.8b \n" // r
2971 "uxtl v19.8h, v19.8b \n" // a
2972 "mul v22.8h, v16.8h, v0.h[0] \n" // B = B * Matrix B
2973 "mul v23.8h, v16.8h, v0.h[4] \n" // G = B * Matrix G
2974 "mul v24.8h, v16.8h, v1.h[0] \n" // R = B * Matrix R
2975 "mul v25.8h, v16.8h, v1.h[4] \n" // A = B * Matrix A
2976 "mul v4.8h, v17.8h, v0.h[1] \n" // B += G * Matrix B
2977 "mul v5.8h, v17.8h, v0.h[5] \n" // G += G * Matrix G
2978 "mul v6.8h, v17.8h, v1.h[1] \n" // R += G * Matrix R
2979 "mul v7.8h, v17.8h, v1.h[5] \n" // A += G * Matrix A
2980 "sqadd v22.8h, v22.8h, v4.8h \n" // Accumulate B
2981 "sqadd v23.8h, v23.8h, v5.8h \n" // Accumulate G
2982 "sqadd v24.8h, v24.8h, v6.8h \n" // Accumulate R
2983 "sqadd v25.8h, v25.8h, v7.8h \n" // Accumulate A
2984 "mul v4.8h, v18.8h, v0.h[2] \n" // B += R * Matrix B
2985 "mul v5.8h, v18.8h, v0.h[6] \n" // G += R * Matrix G
2986 "mul v6.8h, v18.8h, v1.h[2] \n" // R += R * Matrix R
2987 "mul v7.8h, v18.8h, v1.h[6] \n" // A += R * Matrix A
2988 "sqadd v22.8h, v22.8h, v4.8h \n" // Accumulate B
2989 "sqadd v23.8h, v23.8h, v5.8h \n" // Accumulate G
2990 "sqadd v24.8h, v24.8h, v6.8h \n" // Accumulate R
2991 "sqadd v25.8h, v25.8h, v7.8h \n" // Accumulate A
2992 "mul v4.8h, v19.8h, v0.h[3] \n" // B += A * Matrix B
2993 "mul v5.8h, v19.8h, v0.h[7] \n" // G += A * Matrix G
2994 "mul v6.8h, v19.8h, v1.h[3] \n" // R += A * Matrix R
2995 "mul v7.8h, v19.8h, v1.h[7] \n" // A += A * Matrix A
2996 "sqadd v22.8h, v22.8h, v4.8h \n" // Accumulate B
2997 "sqadd v23.8h, v23.8h, v5.8h \n" // Accumulate G
2998 "sqadd v24.8h, v24.8h, v6.8h \n" // Accumulate R
2999 "sqadd v25.8h, v25.8h, v7.8h \n" // Accumulate A
3000 "sqshrun v16.8b, v22.8h, #6 \n" // 16 bit to 8 bit B
3001 "sqshrun v17.8b, v23.8h, #6 \n" // 16 bit to 8 bit G
3002 "sqshrun v18.8b, v24.8h, #6 \n" // 16 bit to 8 bit R
3003 "sqshrun v19.8b, v25.8h, #6 \n" // 16 bit to 8 bit A
3004 "st4 {v16.8b,v17.8b,v18.8b,v19.8b}, [%1], #32 \n" // store 8 ARGB
3005 "b.gt 1b \n"
3006 : "+r"(src_argb), // %0
3007 "+r"(dst_argb), // %1
3008 "+r"(width) // %2
3009 : "r"(matrix_argb) // %3
3010 : "cc", "memory", "v0", "v1", "v2", "v3", "v4", "v5", "v6", "v7", "v16",
3011 "v17", "v18", "v19", "v22", "v23", "v24", "v25");
